{"id":"quant-ph/0603257","submitter":"Filippo Caruso","authors":"Filippo Caruso, Vittorio Giovannetti","title":"Degradability of Bosonic Gaussian channels","comments":"7 pages, 1 figure, 1 table (minor editing)","journal-ref":"Physical Review A 74, 062307 (2006)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.74.062307","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat.other physics.optics","license":null,"abstract":"  The notion of weak-degradability of quantum channels is introduced by\ngeneralizing the degradability definition given by Devetak and Shor. Exploiting\nthe unitary equivalence with beam-splitter/amplifier channels we then prove\nthat a large class of one-mode Bosonic Gaussian channels are either weakly\ndegradable or anti-degradable. In the latter case this implies that their\nquantum capacity Q is null. In the former case instead, this allows us to\nestablish the additivity of the coherent information for those maps which admit\nunitary representation with single-mode pure environment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Mar 2006 14:36:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 21 Jul 2006 16:49:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 10 Oct 2006 10:04:53 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 23 Feb 2007 14:41:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
